  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nIf Keycard was frozen during account recovery, then there will be an incorrect flow for recovery. \r\nThe only workaround is to reopen the app and recover the account with the mnemonic, and select Keycard as the key storage.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/146794971-c061fae3-3b2a-424d-8ec3-650b2fcecc49.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Create or recover a Keycard multi-account \r\n2. Re-install Status or open it on another device\r\n3. Accept Status Terms of Use > `Get started` > `Access existing keys` > `Recover with Keycard` > `Begin recovery`\r\n4. Enter invalid 6-digit passcode 3 times\r\n5. On the `Keycard is frozen` screen tap `Reset with mnemonic` (or `with PUK`, no difference)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThe `Seed phrase` / `PUK` screen is opened\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThe user is prompted for a password again\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 20/12\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
